This paper deals with improving machine translation accuracy by injecting missing information into pre-trained neural machine translation systems. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a black-box approach for injecting the missing information, which involves modifying the underlying model without changing the training data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper performs a fine-grained syntactic analysis of the generated translations, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves analyzing the structure of the generated text.
